<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED15FF97FF54FE25FBFFFE05" box="[199,1149,403,430]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B534515BED15FF97FF54FE25FBFFFE05" blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1221]" box="[199,1149,403,430]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED15FF97FF54FE25FECCFE05" bold="true" box="[199,334,403,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a noun in apposition referring to the 
<typeStatus id="6A30EFF9ED15FF97FC7FFE22FB9EFE06" box="[1004,1052,404,430]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED15FF97FF54FE01FBFAFD96" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B534515BED15FF97FF54FE01FBFAFD96" blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED15FF97FF54FE01FEC0FE79" bold="true" box="[199,322,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males resemble 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED15FF97FD91FE0EFDE3FE79" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[514,609,440,466]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED15FF97FD91FE0EFDE3FE79" box="[514,609,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">C. asper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED15FF97FDFAFE01FD46FE79" bold="true" box="[617,708,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED15FF97FDFAFE01FD46FE79" box="[617,708,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the shape of the palp, but differ from it by the less-developed denticles on the embolic base, the relatively smooth and flat surface of the embolic disc, and the longer retrolateral tibial apophysis (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED15FF97FEC6FE49FE54FDB2" box="[341,470,511,538]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 36–38" captionStart-1="FIGURES 39–41" captionStartId-0="8.[151,264,1034,1058]" captionStartId-1="8.[151,264,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox-0="[298,1286,181,1011]" captionTargetBox-1="[285,1306,1126,1932]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@8.[285,1303,181,1011]" captionTargetId-1="figure-46@8.[280,1308,1119,1935]" captionTargetPageId-0="8" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionText-0="FIGURES 36–38. Palp of Charippus bukittimah Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (36), ventral (37) and retrolateral (38) view." captionText-1="FIGURES 39–41. Palp of Charippus bukittimah Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (39), ventral (40) and retrolateral (41) view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500759" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500761" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6500759/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6500761/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Figs 36–41</figureCitation>
). The female can be distinguished from that of 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED15FF97FC4CFDB6FBBEFDB1" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[991,1084,512,538]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED15FF97FC4CFDB6FBBEFDB1" box="[991,1084,512,538]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">C. asper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED15FF97FBD0FE49FB19FDB1" bold="true" box="[1091,1179,511,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED15FF97FBD0FE49FB19FDB1" box="[1091,1179,511,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the trajectory of the copulatory ducts and the wider EW compared with the width of the vulvae (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED15FF97FC7AFD95FBEFFD96" box="[1001,1133,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURES 42–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1497,1521]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1473]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 42–47. Female genitalia of Charippus bukittimah Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 42–43, 45. Ventral view; 44, 46. Dorsal view; 47. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500767/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Figs 42–46</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED15FF97FF54FDF1FDF9FB09" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" type="description">
<paragraph id="B534515BED15FF97FF54FDF1FB96FC0E" blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED15FF97FF54FDF1FE27FDC9" bold="true" box="[199,421,583,609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED15FF97FD33FDF1FCA6FDC9" box="[672,804,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,1245,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-464@7.[246,1342,1245,1930]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Charippus bukittimah Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (30, 32–33, 35) and female (31, 34). 30–32. Habitus, in dorsal (30–31) and lateral (32) view; 33–34. Front view of carapace; 35. Details left of chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500757/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Figs 30, 32</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 1.40; abdomen length 1.14. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.29, ALE 0.17, PME 0.05, PLE 0.16. Measurements of legs: I 2.37 (0.74, 0.49, 0.52, 0.33, 0.29), II 1.98 (0.65, 0.33, 0.42, 0.31, 0.27), III 2.01 (0.65, 0.28, 0.41, 0.39, 0.28), IV 1.90 (0.61, 0.18, 0.41, 0.43, 0.27). Chelicerae with fang-like projection distally; promargin with two teeth, retromargin with one bicuspid tooth. Palp (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED15FF97FF44FD61FED9FD5A" box="[215,347,727,754]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 36–38" captionStart-1="FIGURES 39–41" captionStartId-0="8.[151,264,1034,1058]" captionStartId-1="8.[151,264,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox-0="[298,1286,181,1011]" captionTargetBox-1="[285,1306,1126,1932]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@8.[285,1303,181,1011]" captionTargetId-1="figure-46@8.[280,1308,1119,1935]" captionTargetPageId-0="8" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionText-0="FIGURES 36–38. Palp of Charippus bukittimah Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (36), ventral (37) and retrolateral (38) view." captionText-1="FIGURES 39–41. Palp of Charippus bukittimah Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (39), ventral (40) and retrolateral (41) view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500759" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500761" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6500759/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6500761/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Figs 36–41</figureCitation>
): embolus coiled for more than a circle; embolic disc large, weakly sclerotized, centrally concave; LED narrow, serrulate-edged; tegulum not obviously sclerotized, tegular lobe present; retrolateral tibial apophysis slightly curved, wide at base and gradually tapered towards tip in retrolateral view, with distal part slightly innerhooked in ventral view. Sternum without setal tuft. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED15FF97FC1CFCF5FB92FCF5" box="[911,1040,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,1245,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-464@7.[246,1342,1245,1930]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Charippus bukittimah Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (30, 32–33, 35) and female (31, 34). 30–32. Habitus, in dorsal (30–31) and lateral (32) view; 33–34. Front view of carapace; 35. Details left of chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500757/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Figs 30, 32</figureCitation>
): carapace reddish brown, cephalon slightly darker, CPSB present, dorsal abdomen pale yellow, with greenish brown markings, not obviously sclerotized; ventral abdomen grayish brown; legs I–II slightly darker than legs III–IV.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B534515BED15FF97FF54FC19FDF9FB09" blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED15FF97FF54FC19FEA7FC61" bold="true" box="[199,293,943,969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Female.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED15FF97FD8EFC19FDF2FC61" box="[541,624,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,1245,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-464@7.[246,1342,1245,1930]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Charippus bukittimah Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (30, 32–33, 35) and female (31, 34). 30–32. Habitus, in dorsal (30–31) and lateral (32) view; 33–34. Front view of carapace; 35. Details left of chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500757/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 1.41; abdomen length 1.31. Chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED15FF97FA90FC19FAD4FC62" box="[1283,1366,943,970]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,1245,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-464@7.[246,1342,1245,1930]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Charippus bukittimah Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (30, 32–33, 35) and female (31, 34). 30–32. Habitus, in dorsal (30–31) and lateral (32) view; 33–34. Front view of carapace; 35. Details left of chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500757/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) as in males but without fang-like projection. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.35, ALE 0.20, PME 0.05, PLE 0.18. Measurements of legs: I 2.24 (0.74, 0.41, 0.53, 0.36, 0.20), II 1.97 (0.63, 0.38, 0.43, 0.28, 0.25), III 2.12 (0.72, 0.30, 0.38, 0.42, 0.30), IV 2.37 (0.82, 0.30, 0.51, 0.45, 0.29). Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED15FF97FC33FBADFC71FB9D" box="[928,1011,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,1245,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-464@7.[246,1342,1245,1930]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Charippus bukittimah Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (30, 32–33, 35) and female (31, 34). 30–32. Habitus, in dorsal (30–31) and lateral (32) view; 33–34. Front view of carapace; 35. Details left of chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500757/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) as in male. Sternum as in male. Epigynum (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED15FF97FF6FFB89FE28FBF2" box="[252,426,1087,1114]" captionStart="FIGURES 42–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1497,1521]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1473]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 42–47. Female genitalia of Charippus bukittimah Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 42–43, 45. Ventral view; 44, 46. Dorsal view; 47. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500767/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Figs 42, 43, 45</figureCitation>
): window large, with sclerotized rims, median septum absent; lateral depressions shallow. Vulva (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED15FF97FF7AFBD5FEEFFBD6" box="[233,365,1123,1150]" captionStart="FIGURES 42–47" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1497,1521]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1473]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 42–47. Female genitalia of Charippus bukittimah Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 42–43, 45. Ventral view; 44, 46. Dorsal view; 47. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500767/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Figs 44, 46</figureCitation>
): CD long and coiled, swerving for nine times; AG small and oval, almost extending anteriorly; spermathecae slightly bulging, peanut-like.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED15FF97FF54FB1DFE63FB6D" box="[199,481,1195,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" type="distribution">
